{"data": {"goal": "Write four focused sensor-level test modules for the TestFailureSensor in-flight dedup mechanism shipped in commit 20baa93a1d. The mechanism lives in backend/core/ouroboros/governance/intake/sensors/test_failure_sensor.py \u2014 read that file and the existing sensor test at tests/governance/intake/sensors/test_test_failure_sensor.py before writing, so the new tests match the project's patterns (pytest-asyncio, stubbed router, explicit env-var setup). If helpful, read the nearby conftest patterns under tests/governance/intake/ for fixture conventions, but do not modify conftest or __init__ files \u2014 all new code must live in the four target test modules below. Each module covers one behavior in isolation: (A) test_test_failure_sensor_dedup.py \u2014 a second signal for the same target within the TTL window is suppressed with the expected 'already in-flight' log line; (B) test_test_failure_sensor_ttl.py \u2014 after TTL expiry the same target is re-admitted and a new op is created; (C) test_test_failure_sensor_isolation.py \u2014 concurrent signals for different target files are not cross-suppressed; (D) test_test_failure_sensor_marker_refresh.py \u2014 the in-flight marker is refreshed on successful enqueue. The TTL default is 60s; read it from the env var the sensor consults rather than hardcoding. Prefer tests that stub the router over tests that boot the full intake layer.", "reason_code": "multi_file_change", "risk_tier": "NOTIFY_APPLY", "target_file": "tests/governance/intake/sensors/test_test_failure_sensor_dedup.py"}, "op_id": "op-019d906d-979f-7ce6-bfd1-787c5a63b79b-cau", "state": "planned", "timestamp": 888.928039208, "wall_time": 1776245443.261744}
